caption: Better try out their yakiniku when full-service resumes! Best in the area
Very nice quality for the price. Pretty legit! Just wish we could dine in because the timing for pickup makes the food not that good as fresh cooked.
It was a delicious sushi. The quality ratio is amazing.
Tried this spot once with my friend and I am hooked ever since. I loved the great atmosphere and tasty dishes and drinks. Great work.
This spot is good! Convenient prices, big dishes and the staff members are always super nice.

(Translated by Google) There are quite a few Japanese people, so I think it's delicious. Yakiniku is also delicious, but if you want to eat sushi, we recommend white tuna at your own risk (the white 4 cans in the middle of the sushi platter in the photo). White tuna is actually called Escolar, a fish that cannot be sold on the market in Japan, but it can be eaten normally here. This is really delicious. But at your own risk. Details should not be written on the restaurant page, so please check it out.  (Original) 結構日本人が来ているので、やっぱり美味しいのだと思います。焼肉も美味しいですが、お寿司を食べるなら自己責任でホワイトツナがおすすめ(写真の寿司盛り合わせの真ん中の白い4カンです)。ホワイトツナは本当はアブラソコムツと言って、日本では市場に回せない魚ですがここでは普通に食べられます。これがめちゃめちゃ美味しい。しかし自己責任で。詳細は飲食店のページに書くべきでない内容ですので、お調べいただければ幸いです。
Wonderful atmosphere and very affable service. The meals were crisp and delicious. Will easily recommend this place to others. Fair prices and big portions. Keep up the great work.
Very well made, high quality Japanese food!
Great atmosphere! Good COVID precautions!
Such a great Bento box lunch deal, always fresh and friendly staff.
I eat here a lot since I work nearby. I love how the customer service is always great and they keep the place well kept constantly. Pricing is affordable and they serve big portions.
Fantastic food, very kind staff, consistently excellent character. They charge reasonable pricing and the food quality is fantastic. Kudos.
We had an excellent  at this spot. We loved the wonderful ambience and the menu. The waiters are super amiable. I am glad we finally decided to visit this restaurant.
The food is always well prepared and flavorful, workers hands out excellent customer service. I loved the cleanliness and atmosphere. Highly recommended.
They offer a nice range of fresh food. I like dining here. Staff members are always super friendly, prices are fair and the place is always well organised.
Delicious food and attentive staff.

One of the best $1 nigiri places in the area. My friends and I have been coming here for years. Sushi is always fresh and the size is average. I always get the salmon, tuna, hamachi, uni, eel and flounder. With Covid, you can only place the order for pick up. My order of +50 pieces took less than 15 minutes. The City of Bethesda has set up tents throughout the week for diners to enjoy food as well. Parking is very easy as theres +3 garages within walking distance and plenty of street parking. If you want great fish at great value this is your spot
Awesome sushi, better price!

This restaurant is absolutely one of the most attractive restaurants in the area. Anytime I come there I am awfully pleased. They always keep their high  standard service and the topmost level of dishes  they give. You no doubt will love this restaurant. Very  recommended.

Honestly have nothing bad to say. All the sushi is so fresh and yummy. The miso soup is just delicious. And the teriyaki chicken is just amazing. And the decor inside the restaurant is so so cute. Satsuma is the most quality Japanese cuisine I’ve ever had.
Awesome and fresh food, I love the vibes this spot has, and the employees were friendly. I will surely come back.
They have raised their prices and taken food away from their dishes.  The servers are poor as I just had one cause soup to spill all over my clothes. They have gone to the toilet. Don't risk it.
Good, inexpensive sushi!  Can't really beat the $1 per piece of sushi.
Loved this place ever since I came here with my boyfriend. The grill your own food is so fun and let's you grill your own meat how you want it. Very polite staff

Food, price and service are fine but the odor lingering in the restaurant was very unpleasant. I don't know what smell it is but I guess it must be a very old place. If I could make it not rude I would've turned around and left immediately. However, the Japanese guy at the counter smelled to me all the time. I didn't want to make him feel bad so I stayed and did my best to finish the food.

This place is my preferred one. I visit plenty of restaurants but to this one I keep coming back again and again. The team is very helpful and the cuisine they offer is so flavorful. I would always prefer to have a decent dinner in this restaurant. I highly recommend this place.
This spot obviously knows how to take care of their clients. Constantly with a nice approach. The food is conveniently priced, constantly delicious and clean.
This place is excellent! Reasonable prices, large dishes and the employees are consistently nice.
Would definitely recommend visiting this place. Exceptional vibes, delicious dishes, great customer service. I recommend this place.
Better than expected, both food and price
The food is pretty good, and the sushi is very reasonably priced. The service for getting the check is quite slow. I would have preferred one more server, which can speed up this process.
My favorite local place for sushi.
Great service. Decent sushi.
The food is amazing. We sat down and instantly someone was there. Our order did not take long, like 5 minutes. The food was amazing and at a good price, this place is one of my favorites.

Giving it a 4 star for the $1 sushi which is pretty decent. I also ordered tonkatsu ramen which was subpar. The pork was quite fatty and the noodle didn't have the chewy texture.  Not the best ramen but they have bento boxes and also Izakaya.
This spot is worth visiting. They serve large portions for fair prices. Always neat and with excellent character. Would recommend to others.
A great $1 per nigiri deal. It's great
Ramen was cold and watered down and the place was not clean.
I love grilling here so much. It is yummy and   cute place. Japanese style. Recommended!!!

Very clean and convenient restaurant. They offer generous meals and for affordable prices. I liked the menu a lot and the waiters were very welcoming and informative. Will definitely recommend this restaurant.
DELICIOUS

From the outside the restaurant had seen better days. Inside we went with the $1 sushi menu and ordered salmon, tuna, fatty tuna, yellow tail, salmon roe, tiny roe, real crab, octopus, scallops, surf clam, sweet shrimp, sea urchin and miso soup. Everything was average but the tuna belly, yellow fin, scallop and sweet shrimp really stood out. Also one of the best miso soup I’ve tasted. I was expecting small cuts of fish because of the $1 special but they didn’t skimp. I enjoyed it and would return.

Worst Japanese food I've had in my entire life. I ordered chicken under the "Fried" catagory thinking I would get something like karagedon. Oh no. What I got was a pan of boiled chicken served in a puddle of water. It was awful. My boyfriend got the miso ramen. It was bland and pathetic as well. Edit: My boyfriend reminded me to add that the entire restaurant smelled of urine. Don't know how I forgot that detail. Probably because it paired with the food so nicely.
They serve big dishes and for fair rates. helpful employees. I recommend this place.
Good Japanese restaurant. Delicious fish
Probably the best Japanese food in this area. Nice staff, service fast and reasonable prices! 🥗🍙🍚🍣

The food is delicious and the staff very attentive and friendly. The space is cute and well organize. The only bummer for me, as a mom, is their changing table situation. The men's restroom has nothing and the women's has two cushioned chairs pushed together and covered with a sheet. This is NOT safe nor sanitary and a sad excuse for a changing table for a baby. I'd like to see them do better with that. Had it not been for that, my review would have been 5 stars.
This was my second time here. Enjoyed the food very much! Great vibe in the restaurant. Would highly recommend to anyone who enjoys Japanese cuisine, or an active duty member who misses the culture.
(Translated by Google) There are vegetarian ramen, vegetarian noodles 👍  (Original) 有素食拉麵，vegetarian noodles 👍

Went with a group of 10 that was well handled. Wait staff was always close by to help out if needed. Menu was decent for a small restaraunt. Prices were fair and it was a good overall experience.  Will visit again soon.
I just had my lunch around 2:30 today. I started vomit right after I'm back to office. Something must be wrong. Now I'm typing after I threw up.
Very authentic Japanese style foods. The point is, they are not expensive!
sushi is ok, but ramen tastes weird. not japanese at all.
Good Japanese food. The inner room has traditional seating with low benches, and you have to remove your shoes. Apart from cheap sushi, the barbecue on the table is good.
Reasonable price, delicious food and good service!!!!!
This is our dinner spot every time we visit DC.  Traditional and Authentic....what more can you ask for?  It is out of our way but very worth the drive.
quick service and food was pretty darn good

This is a traditional Japanese noodle/sushi/bento box restaurant. Very reasonably priced, clean, and tasty food.  Good lunch specials. But don't expect to practice your Japanese because mostly all of the servers are Thai. Still good service.
Love the BBQ. Nigiri is also always good quality
Watered down bland broth ramen, no life in these noodles, subpar pork meat (hardly any). I expected more from Bethesda. The one dollar nigiri was alright, but portions were small.

They have the best sashimi I ever had in my life. The quality of the fish, and food in general is just incredible! The prices are very affordable. If you are not in the mood for sushi, you can have Korean barbecue, in Japanese style, with all types of high quality meat and veggies. Perfect for a date or a night out with your family and friends.
Excellent sushi, very reasonably priced
The sushi was certainly much better than I expected!

Sushi rolls we're incredibly small and they had a small selection of non-cooked sushi. VERY little vegetarian options. Messed up our bill, too. Overcharged us.  But very friendly, clean and nice atmosphere.  Grilled rice ball was very tasty.

Sanitation is very basic of culinary. Almost all seat cushions are stained and looks 5years old. Mine was grey cushion but still noticeably filthy. other lighter colors were worse. Curtain's white colored part is brown with human protein. I just don't understand how come this happens. Sushi wasn't good, ramen was ...I never had that kind japanese ramen in last 4 years. It was that bad.
Favorite ramen and authentic Japanese food in Bethesda. Good value.

Even though the service was pretty good, the food quality was below average.  I was walking around Bethesda and came across this restaurant. I never heard of this place before so I decided to come check it out for lunch.  It's has 2 sides to it. One side is by the actual entrance and it is surrounded by windows so it was super bright in the room. The other side appeared to have limited windows and they were covered. It was much darker. I think this side was for bigger parties.  I ordered a donburi lunch special which came with miso soup. Honestly, the miso soup was the best part of my meal. The donburi itself didn't have much meat (I ordered beef). It had a lot of mushrooms, vegetables, and red ginger. Man the ginger was disgusting. I hate ginger. I didn't know there would be so much in it. Also the actual food only filled up half my bowl - and the bowl wasn't even that big! It was just poorly assembled imo. They need to put more food in the bowls with more meat!  Nonetheless, the service was good. My waiter kept checking up on me and was helpful when I was deciding what to eat. This is the only reason why I'm not giving a 1 Star.

This is not the place you go out of your way to eat at. However, if you are in the area and want great food for the price then this is your spot.  I've never had a bad experience. The staff isn't particularly attentive but they get the job done. Did I mention the sushi is really cheap?

Good Japanese restaurant!!! Japanese living in DC gather frequently, so this is admitted good authentic Japanese restaurant by Japanese people!!! You can enjoy sushi, Japanese style bbq and small plates called “otsumami”. You can enjoy with saki so much!!! Especially you can enjoy sushi with incredible cheap price!!! There are sushi counter and kotatsi seats besides regular tables. Very good restaurant. Of course you can choose good saki from alcohol menu. When I visited, many Japanese groups was enjoying their party!!!!! So I will go again for sure!!!!!
Food is delicious, I really liked the place
My toddler son's favorite Japanese restaurant in the world!  Can't beat their dollar sushi happy hour every night!
$1 Nigiri night was great. Good nigiri at a very reasonable price for the area left me full and quite happy.
Absolutely awesome!!! Nicest staff in the world. My wife and I come here about 2-3 times a week. According to my wife, "Anytime is a good time for Ramen!"
Excellent foodie experience.

The best Japanese restaurant in the area. My softball team has been going here for years (we're a Japanese international team). Majority of the Japanese in the area come to this location. Food is not only authentic, but very reasonably priced.  The front has a sit-down area for light eats while the back has a sushi bar area and more traditional seating. Brings me back to Japan while taking off shoes and sitting down for a nice nomikai.  Highly recommend the sushi, ramen, bbq, and of course, Sapporo/Kirin ichiban beer!
I used to like this restaurant. However, recently, the ramen quality went down a lot. The servers should NOT wear strong perfume - I lost my appetite after smelling it.
Food is okay and not expensive.
Good ramen and cheap decent $1 sushi.
Absolutely amazing for the price ($1 sushi is epic) and all around very good. I wish I had a place this good at something like this price point in Manhattan.
Awesome!!!

My friends and I were there tonight. However, our experience wasn’t as pleasant as others. We all noticed it was a busy night. We walkined in around 7:30 pm and no one even took our order. I had a Diet Coke and that’s it. I left couple bucks and we left at 8pm and went to another restaurant...

This place really doesn't deserve 4 stars.. Food is at best mediocre, but over priced for what it is. Rolls are made with too wet rice, meat was chewy, salad and soup was flavorless. Service was absolutely terrible. Water and tea were never refilled even though cups were all empty, server never came to check on us, and I had to waive at one of them to finally get a check. I will never return here since there are so many restaurants near by that are better quality and cheaper cost.
The food was AMAZING! They even made sure to cook everything as requested to avoid all of my mom's food allergies. They were attentive and super friendly!
Service was so bad that we didn't get order. Stood around for about 10 minutes for a table, then another 10 minutes to get water.
Amazing
Nice place for lunch
Needs a serious cleaning to start. Staff friendly, but the sushi was not good. Would not recommend.
Exalet noodle Raman best anywhere in Montgomery County
The $1 nigiri sushi is great value.  I had the tonkotsu ramen and it wasn't very good.  Restaurant is very hot, but still busy which means I'll probably return to explore the menu a bit more
Good food and good service. A very nice Japanese restaurant with reasonable price. My favorite is their happy hour ramen.
I love this place! All the staff are so friendly and they have really good food!
If just getting sushi it is decently priced. Has very good food though. Spice ramen was not as spicy as it looks.
Great sushi at an even better value I go here at least once a month because bethesda is kind of far But totally worth the trip for the sushi @satsuma
Nice place great Sushi great price!!
Good food.  But cutting back on portion is a bad idea.
Reasonable price and authentic taste. This place is very popular among Japanese living (working) nearby.
The $1 Nigiri is the move at this place, a far better deal than some of the Maki. Also recommend the Dango for dessert.

Food ok, staff friendly and helpful. I am concerned that more and more restaurants feel as if they are doing customer's a favor rather than appreciating that we are spending our hard earned $$'s eating there.  A minor request turned into a "we'll do it for you this time but when we're busy we can't accomodate"...all I ask was for my hamachi toro sushi to be torched !! How hard is that ???????  Will not be returning. Hamachi kama was not very fresh.
Fantastic sushi, $1 nigiri ALL THE TIME, yum.
You must reserve to have Japanese style BBQ. If you cannot seat BBQ seat, it is questionable whether it is worth to come here from Washington DC.
The $1 unagi is the best I've ever had. And I've eaten it all over Nippon.
Love their sushi. Always fresh and tasty! The pricing is affordable. Highly recommend!
Slow slow slow service and very overpriced

Good service and quick during lunch rush.  Ramen was pretty good, although I can't say I care for sweet corn in it. What stood out for me were the pork gyozas.  Should make a trip there for those alone.

A cozy Japanese barbecue restaurant serving inexpensive sushi and decent quality meats & seafood for table top grilling. Friendly and hard-working waitresses kept up with Saturday dinner crowd although they could use extra hands. A good place for family and casual couple dining.
Great sushi and very good ramen.
Everything was great.
They have great sushi for $1 per piece! Can't beat that. I had a good experience here.
Solid ramen and $1 nigiri sushi is great. Food is reasonably priced and quite good. Service was  satisfactory but nothing exceptional.
favorite sushi spot
Good food

Nice restaurant. The service is nice when you get any. They should consider extending their dessert menu because there is not much on it. But a warning, good luck trying to get in at the cooking tables on weekends and friday. They will lie and say that you need a reservation and that its reservation only. It was not until my fiancé went in by himself to try and request a table that they let him. Needless to say, we chose to eat there anyway and were rushed out and given the check when we actually wanted more. Mind you, there wasn't a party coming in. What a shame.
Good authentic Japanese foods,excellent.
A premium karubi is so nice, but expensive...
Lovely place for excellent quality favorites. Many windows. Very sunny. Cozy. Attentive staff. Always tasty.
Some of the best ramen in the area. Love it!
Excellent! And, frankly the only Yakiniku place in the DC Metro area. They also have cheaply priced sushi which is a huge plus!

HOW DO YOU SCREW UP RAW MEAT!!! I would not recommend the meat in the grilling section of the restaurant. Also they charge way to much. It isn't worth $20 for a plate of meat. For a Japanese restaurant I would recommend 'Raku' or 'Tako Grill' those are good high quality choices and don't break the bank.
Best in DC

1.  Service - Quick, friendly, & attentive. 2.  Taste of food and quality of food - Great ramen in MD.  Portion size was just enough & not too salty.  I recommend the Tonkatsu broth with thick noodles.  The $1 sushi is pretty good as well. 3.  Ambiance/decor - Cozy with modern decor.  Not too noisy when busy. 4.  Cleanliness - Looked & felt clean throughout.

This by far the best value for Japanese food in Bethesda. The Tonsokatsu Ramen was good, not packaged and it had real spicy pork in it.  The $1 sushi was of high quality.  This is not a fancy place.  But I kinda like the vibe.  It has happy hour prices for regular dinner service.
My favorite sushi place. It is small and cozy with great food. $1 dollar sushi is a great and delicious deal. My only complaint is sometimes you'll be waiting a while for your food.
Dollar nigiri sushi was great, and really good ramen. (Actual soup not the packet kind!)

Best nigiri sushi for the value! $1 sushi rocks on in Bethesda! Sea urchin, scallop, yellow tail belly, Salmon roe, maguro, red clam sushi, all $1 each! I once had 40 of them and I was very happy the quality and consistency they are offering.  Service drops down in busy time, you will need to wait a long time for service because they are under-staffed. But their grill and sushi are still top-notch. About the Japanese grill, their system is very authentic, they use the kind of Japanese grill that has smoke absorption around the ring of the stove and your clothes will not be smoked to smell. It's probably imported from Japan. And the fact that you will see Japanese customers once in a while tells me they are quite authentic too. Definitely check out their beef tongue, ribeye options for the grill, they are marinated perfectly and the meat quality is stunning. Top with a Sapporo or Asahi. I crave for their food about once a month or so. Sake is great too. But overall, you do need to expect to pay some, not exactly cheap, but for the value, I think it's reasonable and worth it.
Most authentic Japanese place I have been in US so far. Great ramens, mediocre sushi.
Great sushi special!
Ramen not bad and $1 sushi pretty good. good service.

Solid food although nothing unique, but great for families and kids. I love the ramen and young kids split the chicken teriyaki. Sat at the BBQ tables once and enjoyed it, although I prefer Korean BBQ to Japanese.
Nice sushi place just a little off the main drag.
Great spot for Ramen and sushi.
Delicious hot Tonkatsu Ramen with sliced pork.  Yum.
Great food, excellent service, and if you can, try eating in the barbeque room.  Will go back again with my children next time.

I go here several times a month for lunch, and always enjoy it. The food is fresh and good, although be warned that the service is excruciatingly slow. Sometimes the kitchen gets backed up and orders take more than half an hour to be brought out (sometimes with no explanation), and getting the check almost always requires a great deal of patience since the servers are often not even visible - regardless of how many customers are present. Soups and salads and tea are usually brought out quickly though, and if you resign yourself to the fact that lunch will not be quick, the food and atmosphere are very enjoyable. I have tried their sushi, sashimi, BBQ, soups, etc. and liked all of them. My Japanese friends also tell me that this is the most authentic place that they have seen in this part of Bethesda. Overall: if you can stand the slow service, this restaurant is quite good, but if you require a quick lunch, then go elsewhere.
Get the ramen. it will blow your mind.  very authentic menu

This is our favorite sushi restaurant in Bethesda. The fish is the freshest around - and consistently so. We visit a couple of times a month. They also have some nice sakes in case you want a break from beer. We had been going here for some time before someone mentioned that they are known for their ramen, so we finally tried it and were delighted.

Food was decent for a Japanese place (we did do the BBQ) but not impressive. The atmosphere is great, with all sorts of neat wall hangings. However, the service killed it for us. At lunch time, we were seated over for the BBQ and then virtually forgotten. Brought out the plate of meat and left without lighting the hot plate. After waiting an age and a half, they finally came and took care of it...then they ignored us and our water glasses for the rest of the time, despite probably having the largest bill of anyone out for lunch at that time.
